[SN]TITLE[SN]
Funders back 200 single wind turbines across Highlands

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Finance firm Scottish Equity Partners has said it will invest up to Â£9m in a scheme to erect as many as 200 wind turbines across the Highlands and Islands.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The project to create the single-turbine sites would be led by Hamsin Wind.
Farmers and other landowners would install the small turbines near their properties.
The machines involved would not measure more than 20 metres (65ft) high.
